# .scrub_allowlist — regex suppression list for scripts/scrub_check.sh
# One regex per line; lines starting with # are ignored.
# A finding is suppressed if the full "file:line:content" string matches any entry here.
#
# TODO (migration day — see docs/migration_runbook.md):
#   - Remove the migration_runbook.md entries once that file is updated to use
#     YOUR_VPS_HOST and YOUR_USERNAME placeholders.
#   - Remove the getting_started.md entry once that URL is updated post-migration.

# docs/migration_runbook.md: Chris's VPS IP appears in SSH commands throughout.
# These are migration-specific instructions; file becomes generic post-migration.
docs/migration_runbook\.md:.*204\.168\.167\.19

# docs/migration_runbook.md + docs/getting_started.md: payindaman-wq is the
# migration target account and current template publisher URL.
docs/migration_runbook\.md:.*payindaman
docs/getting_started\.md:.*payindaman

# research/, fleet/, published/ YAML files: machine-generated bot parameter files.
# Officer names (FREYA, ODIN, etc.) appear as internal metadata written by the system,
# not as user-facing config that would confuse fork operators.
(research|fleet|published)/.*:.*\b(ODIN|MIMIR|FREYA|LOKI|TYR|VIDAR|HEIMDALL)\b
# docs/troubleshooting.md: shows payindaman-wq upstream URL in sync troubleshooting steps
docs/troubleshooting\.md:.*payindaman
